n footsteps</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 18</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>æ bajvæd Tulabeg ordægæj Fæsnælmæ fæccudæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>по своим свежим следам Тулабег оттуда отправился в Фаснал</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>from there Tulabeg left for Fæsnæl in his own footsteps</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 122</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*upā-padam</w> <gloss><q>по следу</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>pati-padam</w> <gloss><q>на прежнее место</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="peo"><w>ni-padiy</w> <gloss><q>вслед</q></gloss></mentioned>, . См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæd"/> 'след'.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It probably traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*upā-padam</w> <gloss><q>in the footsteps</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>pati-padam</w> <gloss><q>to a former place</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="peo"><w>ni-padiy</w> <gloss><q>following</q></gloss></mentioned>, . See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæd"/> ‘footstep’.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>